# NRGX Labs — Autonomous Dev Access

## Live Site

- **URL**: https://app.nrgxlabs.com
- **Invite Code**: RAVEN-BETA-2026
- **Note**: the legacy `raven-tech.co` domain has been retired and is no longer owned. Do not reference it anywhere in code, comments, links, tests, or workflows. The org name is **NRGX Labs**; the repo directory is still `raven-tech/` for historical reasons but that's just disk layout.

## Deployment

- **Repo**: git@github.com:jbsgoneflying/raventech.git (branch: main)
- **Droplet path**: /opt/breach-algo
- **Deploy trigger**: Push to main triggers GitHub Actions (`.github/workflows/deploy.yml`)
- **Manual deploy** (if GH Actions unavailable): SSH into Droplet via DO console, run:
  `cd /opt/breach-algo && git pull && docker compose up -d --build app`
- **Health check**: `curl -sf https://app.nrgxlabs.com/api/health` (public, no auth)

## Browser Testing Workflow

When testing the live site with the browser MCP tool:

1. Navigate to https://app.nrgxlabs.com
2. If redirected to /login, fill the invite code field with `RAVEN-BETA-2026` and submit
3. After login, navigate to the target page
4. Use browser_snapshot before any interaction to get element refs

## Autonomous Dev Cycle

When building a feature:

1. Make code changes in Cursor
2. `git add . && git commit -m "description" && git push origin main`
3. Wait ~90s for GitHub Actions to deploy
4. Test via browser MCP (login if needed, navigate, interact, verify)
5. If issues: fix, push, re-test
6. Report to user when ready

## Architecture Quick Reference

- **Backend**: Python FastAPI (`backend/app.py` is the main file, ~4,900 lines)
- **Frontend**: Vanilla JS — page-specific scripts in `static/` with shared helpers in `static/ui_kit.js`
- **Docker**: single `app` service, gunicorn + uvicorn, port 8000, behind nginx
- **Redis**: session state + engine caches
